list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Added duration to the clock-out procedure

task.summary: Default task
I have the button switches working and some of the bugs worked out of the start and stop time stuff. Still very early.
Added some graphic elements
Fixed some button state elements.

Through some ham-fisted bullshittery the clock in and clock out system is functioning. There are lots of holes and things that probably will not work they way it is setup now. But... that will get fixed.
Found a few new hurdles to overcome. Have some of the messaging systems starting to work.
Fixed a bug (I think) in the Task drop down. And got some basic stuff working for the runtime counter
I have to rework how I'm sharing the timesheet between stuff.
Got the main running time counter to work. Found a flaw in the Switch system. It runs the clock with the last timesheet even if it doesn't create a timesheet

Got the clock running error fixed, but discovered another bug-issue. The Task list is still not properly updating with all of the tasks. JazzBand project - Casino asset has 10 tasks. None were listed. Have to find out why.
Fixed an issue with the switch not running the clock
Got the timer and the Upper monitor to work.
Got a lot of new things done in the UI and system. Still can't get the drop downs to be clean. Nonetheless, the basic in and out system is working.
Back that ass up
I'm trying to make the date counters REALLY dynamic, but it's not working. I'm going to a more hard-wired approach just to make it work, but I wanted to save a copy of this before I revert.
Got the date rollers working. Last major functional bit is the clocks. Then there's the pop-ups for setting the dates manually, and fixing the drop-downs
I figured out how to GET the dials to all rotate, now I just have to get that to actually work in the system.
Got the clocks to work, although there is some minor translational crap going on, and the images get a little aliasy while running. Not really a problem for now.
Added duration to the clock-out procedure
Still have to figure out the meter dials, but for the most part it is working.
I found an irritating bug with the tasks setup. They don't work right. Also, Switching with error-checks still clocks you out, instead of just rejecting the button push.
Fixed the task menu issue
The solution to the tasks list has arisen a new bug. I'm using this commit to find differences.

Revert "Fixed the task menu issue"

Ok, after fuckering and unfuckering it, a few things in the UI got broken. Hopefully they're no big deal to fix. Deal with it in the morning.
Fixed my bug issues. Separated out the Top Output into individual outputs, so I'm not cramming everything through one pipe each time.
Fixed the exit error for the loops and also got the window position to save so it opens in the same place.
Got the two meters to work pretty damned well. The week time may still be off by a little bit, but we'll get back to that
Ok. Made significant progress getting everything to work smoothly. All dials and meters seem to be working correctly. Clock in checks are working. Next...
Integrating the TARDIS SystemTray into the Time Lord
Blending the Tardis and Time Lord. Have an icon made. System tray works, and launches Time Lord. No mouse detectors built in yet.
Changes made from home, plus I converted the logging system to be independent of the configuration. Who wants to manually set a log file?
Got the rudimentary lunch timer to work. Still needs proper functionality
Created a Burger King Colors inspired Lunch pop up and figured out a little more of the lunch pop up.
Got my pop up tests to work. Just need to port this over to the main tardis

I've made some progress on the Lunch timer. Fixed the issue with older time sheets crapping out due to 'days' as part of the time. Might have to convert the chronograph in the tardis to a class and QtThread instead of function and python thread.
I attempted to get a QThread to work in here. It still might, but for the moment, I'm going to run back to the thread I had. This one seems to conflict with the underlying engine.
Got the lunch pop up working! Had to simplify the Tardis a bit and make it a launcher only. All tools will have to be able to run independently of the tardis.
Some fine tuning of the triggers has been done and the lunch pop up seems to be fully functional at the moment.
Set the lunch times to be a little more accurate
Building out the End of Day window

The EOD clock out system seems to be working. And the lunch break seems to be working. I need a pop up that tells people in the morning that they're not clocked in. Maybe something that does it every few minutes.

So, the time lord utility has a flaw that I'll have to work around. There's no refresh for external clock outs. Thus, when the EOD system clocks out, if the users still has their time lord open, it's just going to fuck up.
I've got a few more things fixed. The Main UI still doesn't update when the sub ui's or other processes clock out the user. I'll get it fixed.
Fixed the task refresh and independent launcher issue.
